Arsenal are only three signings away from winning the title and should start by pinching Chelsea goalkeeper Petr Cech
according to former Gunners midfielder Ray Parlour
Cech is likely to be watching from the substitutes bench when Arsenal face Chelsea at the Emirates Stadium on Sunday
Jose Mourinho 's men are 10 points clear going into the game this weekend but Parlour believes signing Cech in the summer can help Arsenal overcome the Blues next year
Parlour believes the Gunners should sell Wojciech Szczesny in order to sign Cech this summer
